cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV, cs.CL 

This paper deals with the issue of learning abstract and systematic relations in neural networks, which is a common problem in machine learning and falls under the category of "Learning" (cs.LG). The paper proposes a solution using Bayesian weight priors, which involves probabilistic modeling and inference, making it relevant to "Artificial Intelligence" (cs.AI) and "Neural and Evolutionary Computing" (cs.NE). The experiments involve image classification, which falls under "Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition" (cs.CV) and natural language processing, which falls under "Computation and Language" (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses more on the learning aspect, the first three categories are more likely to be relevant.
